        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'
 nowrap><b><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'>harrije</font></b></td>
        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> An update from Rich:</P><P><BLOCKQUOTE id=quote><font size=2 face="Verdana" id=quote>quote:<hr height=1 noshade id=quote><BR> Thanks for the feedback, I think there were a lot of good points made and I appreciate the time people took to post.</P><P>In the next Test patch, pets will use their owner's resist scores and level ,except when they have better scores of their own. If the pet's own resistance is higher, than it uses it's innate resistance against that type of spell. If the owner has a higher score, the pet uses that instead.</P><P>For example, fire elemental pets have incredibly high fire resistance, but low resistance to other type of magic. If someone tries to cast a fire based spell on this pet, it will use it's innate fire resistance because it's so high. If someone tries to cast a poison spell on the pet, it will use it's owner's current poison resistance score instead.</P><P>Thanks again for the comments and opinions,</P><P>- Rich<BR><hr height=1 noshade id=quote></BLOCKQUOTE id=quote></font id=quote><font face="Verdana" size=2 id=quote></P><P>That looks to preserve situational utility but still overall increase the durability of pets in most normal fighting and raid-level encounters. </P><P>I hope it tests well, because I like the idea in principle. It is a scalar change: if you take the time to level up and to improve your equipment, your pet will grow right along with you. A level 50 in basic planar gear isn't going to see nearly the improvement as a level 60 with high-end Velious and Luclin gear, but then the level 50 doesn't <i>need</i> much of an upgrade. It's the level 60 who is falling further and further behind the curve compared to the rest of his guild.</P><P>If I were to add one change, it would be to have pets <i>cast</i> spells at the master's level as well. Current pets are too low level to land spells on some very high-end mobs, and that is a sizeable damage penalty for pet classes that goes above and beyond the general difficulty of the mobs.</P><P></P><P>Edited by - harrije on 07/19/2002  06:53:01</font></td>
      </tr>
